winning_structure.name: UBX-AID-ALM
winning_structure.description: GPS aiding almanac input/output message. This message can be used to send almanac data to the receiver or to poll for it. The message length can be either 8 bytes (containing 'svid' and 'week' only) or 40 bytes (including the 'dwrd' block), depending on whether the almanac data is available (indicated by the 'week' field).

fields.name: svid
fields.description: SV ID for which this Almanac Data is (Valid Range: 1 .. 32 or 51, 56, 63).

fields.name: week
fields.description: Issue Date of Almanac (GPS week number). If this value is 0, the 'dwrd' block (Almanac Words) is typically not sent by the receiver, resulting in an 8-byte message.

fields.name: dwrd
fields.description: Almanac Words. This block is optional and typically not sent by the receiver if 'week' is 0, reducing the overall message length to 8 bytes.
